reviews.review:
I am just baffled by this movie.  Waited so long for it, and now frustrated after watching it.  The writing is mediocre at best, acting and story are all over the place.  Just a big disappointment.

Updated: Saw second time, now I see how bad the plot holes are.  No excuse for how badly written the final Star Wars movie is.
It’s a great closure to a very underwhelming trilogy.

Overall, the movie did the franchise justice, although not perfect it was a satisfying end to the saga. No need to over analyze, just try to enjoy the entertainment. Good acting, great action, and amazing special effects. UPDATE: Now after seeing the movie a few times, I like more each time. It truly is a great movie, and if the TLJ didn't waste so much time on the story this movie would feel less rushed. Adam and Daisy are just great actors and are so good in their characters Im left wanting more.

The film was comprised of pretty much nothing but whiplash-inducing pacing that rarely lets things settle for the audience, retcons that disrespect some of the most inspired themes from its predecessors, and plot holes so bad that they not only make the emotional dilemmas of the previous movies completely inconsequential, but they contradict the mythology of the whole series.

Don't get me wrong, the acting and the chemistry between the performances is the best it could have been given the material, the audiovisual presentation was inspired as always, it was funny a decent amount of times, some of the new side characters were precious, the set-pieces were impressive, a couple of scenes managed to be incredibly impactful, and Kylo Ren still manages to be one of the greatest characters in the franchise. In the end though, this turned out to be a disappointing mess and a clear indicator of how poorly planned this trilogy was. Worst Star Wars movie ever.
I loved it!  everything was great!  no complaints!  Amazing end to the story!
Daisy Ridley’s Rey is absolutely wonderful. Adam Driver’s Kylo Ren is phenomenal- all the acting was really well done. And of course, never underestimate a droid :)
I wanted to enjoy it but it lacks heart and soul in the story The actors are all great! But the dialogue was just explaining what they are doing and why. Show me don't tell me.

The movie keeps your interest but there is no scene in the movie I desire to see again. Everything was too forced and Rushed and not very well planned. If you Know nothing of Star wars then it gets a B. Unfortunately most know Star Wars and therefore it gets a D. Some nostalgic moments and a few feel good moments. Great to see Carrie Fisher again done tastefully. Disney did a horrible job if they were really trying to honor What George Lucas has done. Its just a movie and a story line that wrecks everything Lucas and the first six movies gave us. No reason to see it twice. Rogue one was the best thing Disney gave to Star Wars. Thats about it.
Best of the new trilogy by far!
